# Python conventions (Ledgerlens)

Applies when creating or editing Python files. The package layout is created in
Phase 0 per `docs/PHASE_0_BUILD.md` and design doc section 11; these conventions
govern it from the first file.

## The seam pattern (enforce strictly)
- Depend on the abstract interfaces in `ledgerlens/interfaces/` — `Embedder`,
  `Reranker`, `LLMClient` — obtained via `ledgerlens/interfaces/factory.py`
  (`get_embedder()`, `get_reranker()`, `get_llm()`).
- NEVER import or call a vendor SDK (voyageai, sentence_transformers, litellm, etc.)
  outside its interface implementation. Selecting a model/provider is a config change
  in `config.py` / `.env`, never code scattered across modules.
- Real backend implementations lazy-import their heavy SDK inside methods so the
  default `fake` backends stay dependency-free.

## Stack & style
- Python 3.12. FastAPI + Pydantic v2. Type everything; prefer typed request/response models.
- Configuration is centralized in `config.py` (pydantic-settings) — the single source of
  truth. Don't hardcode model names, endpoints, or backends elsewhere.
- Secrets live in `.env` (gitignored). Never hardcode API keys.

## Dependencies come online per phase
- Install only the phase's group from `pyproject.toml` optional-deps:
  `pip install -e '.[ingestion]'`, `'.[storage]'`, `'.[rerank]'`, `'.[llm]'`, etc.
- Don't pull a dependency group before its phase needs it.

## Before declaring done
- `python scripts/smoke_test.py` (expect GREEN) and `pytest` must pass.
